      "side": 1,
      "message": "I wonder if we should use \"anyOf\" https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/concurrent/CompletableFuture.html#anyOf-java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture...-  instead of a latch here. It seems that if we did that, we could potentially use a single thread to wait for all the ongoing connections. Give that the java17+ JVM does not handle high thread counts very well, this could provide a significant scalability boost by only using 2 threads instead of 3 per connection.",
