      "writtenOn": "2026-05-18T18:27:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I suspect that if we had an isolated thread pool for the forward() connections, and ensured the maxlimit was even numbered, it would at least avoid issues with that pool? That still feel optimistic, counting on the forward() threads to always start and complete in pairs. It would be better if we could somehow have a threadpool that always provided pairs of threads.",
